subject: "Quikscript Outpost" at new location, https://quikscript.neocities.org/quik.htm
msgSnippet: My website, Quikscript Outpost, is now at a new (hopefully permanent) location: https://quikscript.neocities.org/quik.htm
messageBody:
My website, "Quikscript Outpost," is now at a new (hopefully permanent) location: https://quikscript.neocities.org/quik.htm.

Why is it at a new location? The TL;DR version is because the ISP for where it was hosted is apparently ending website support for certain types of subscribers by April 2020 but that they've effectively ended it a lot sooner due to a server migration in March 2019 that they would appear to have botched to some degree. Rather than electing to fight to get it reinstated for all of a year before all support ends (or paying additional money per month so that I may migrate it to their new approved server environment), I have decided to simply place the website onto a new platform (neocities.org).

Over the coming days, I will continue to tweak the site to ensure that everything works properly. If anyone finds anything broken, please let me know. Thank you.
